The Federal Government has informed FIFA of its decision to recognize the Amaju-Pinnick- led Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) as the only football governing  body in the country. The Special Assistant to Vice-President on Media, Laolu Akande, disclosed the decision in a tweet on Monday. “Government will also continue to work with all relevant stakeholders involved to resolve dispute in a timely manner. “Federal Government is upholdiing NFF treaty and obligations to FIFA,” Akande stated.